  "summary": "forge-jsxy 1.0.107: install-time agent script and base64-encoded deployment data warrant human review",
  "details": "The package ships a postinstall agent script (scripts/postinstall-agent.mjs) and several runtime modules (dist/relayServer.js, dist/discordRelayUpload.js, dist/secretScan/*, dist/hfCredentials.js, dist/deploymentDefaults.js) that combine base64-decoding of embedded blobs, outbound network calls (including to huggingface.co and Discord-relay endpoints), and shell/ping invocations. Pattern matches were found on Buffer.from(..., 'base64') decoding alongside POST/fetch/ping primitives and a postinstall lifecycle script, but the specific data flows — what is decoded, where the decoded bytes go, and whether anything attacker-controlled is executed at install time — could not be confirmed from the available evidence. Combined with the package name's potential confusion with other ecosystems and the presence of credential-handling, secret-scanning, and Discord-relay modules, the surface is broad enough that automated classification is not safe without manual inspection of the postinstall script and the base64 payloads.",
